<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-11-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-11-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="1371" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1371">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/911.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Parker</persName>,
                                representing American interests in Mexico, to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-22">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 22, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>161. My 59, September 8. Department of Finance published yesterday an
                            authorization to governors of states to collect the proportionable tax
                            on mines corresponding to each state on Mexican gold basis, which
                            implies a further increase on the recently augmented tax.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Parker.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>